The bug has been successfully fixed! Here's a summary of what was done:

## Problem Analysis
The bug was in the `processResponseHeaders` method in `HttpConnection.java`. The method was supposed to combine multiple values for the same header name with commas (as per HTTP specification RFC 2616), but it was only taking the first value (`values.get(0)`) instead of combining all values.

## Solution
I modified the code to iterate through all header values and combine them with commas:

```java
} else { // combine same header names with comma: http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec4.2
    if (!values.isEmpty()) {
        StringBuilder headerBuf = new StringBuilder();
        for (int i = 0; i < values.size(); i++) {
            if (i > 0)
                headerBuf.append(", ");
            headerBuf.append(values.get(i));
        }
        header(name, headerBuf.toString());
    }
}
```

## Verification
- The triggering test `org.jsoup.helper.HttpConnectionTest::sameHeadersCombineWithComma` now passes
- The code compiles successfully 
- The patch is in standard diff format

The fix correctly implements the HTTP specification requirement to combine multiple header values with commas, which was the expected behavior in the failing test case.

